#######################################################################
#                           Issues with i3                            #
#######################################################################
# Here are the issues. Otherwise, it is very functional wm and not buggy. I like the simple configuration options.
# * [ ] Firefox (pushbullet) notification does not honor xfce4-notifyd settings
# * [ ] No native maximize (for firefox at least) (not fullscreen) support
#
# * [ ] [still ok] Keep the current mode ('resize' etc) printed while we are on the mode
# * [ ] [would be nice] Cycle through all windows of a particular kind (e.g. zathura)
# * [ ] [what would be use really?] Save current window layout and load it (?)
#
# * [?] [Not ideal, turning off mouse_focus] Focus jumps to mouse location after using rofi's window shift
# * [x] [compiled xfce4-i3-workspace plugin][critical window color needed for xfce4 panel] Urgent windows looking for attention that show up in another workplace is invisible in xfce4-panel
# * [x] [wrote my own with i3get] No native alt+tab support, workaround hasn't been working
# * [x] [use rofi] Font for i3 input prompt
# * [x] [xfce4-notifyd settings] DBus notifications stay too long
# * [?] [probably that is the expected behavior] Maximizing any manpage on terminal does not re-arrange the text
# * [x] [xfsettingsd] xfce4-panel colorscheme is not same as xfce4
# * [x] [xfsettingsd] Shift+Print does not work as intended
# * [x] [xfsettingsd] External monitor connection
# * [x] Wasting screen space for title text even when the status bar is present. It is possible to remove the title text, but then the information of the containers is not easy to guess.
# * [x] Moving windows through containers is unpredictable
# * [x] [Couldn't reproduce, seems like xfce4-panel works fine] Using xfce4-panel is possible instead of limited i3 panel. However, the workspace number is added on a as-needed basis, which confuses xfce4-panel's workspace numbering system. So, it is impossible to use xfce4-terminal with i3 workspaces. It is possible to install a i3 applet for xfce4-terminal, but the ppa is non-responsive and compiling from source is  too complicated.
# * [x] No window border between xfce4-terminal windows (turn on 'Pref > Appearances > Border on new window)
# * [x] Mod+hjkl should stop when scrolling through window (should not cycle)
